<!-- 
    MULTIPLE-DESIGN REFERENCE CODE
    BY PANDAPPUCCINO
    
    == WHAT IS THIS? ==
    Some of my characters have multiple designs (such as my FFXIV OC, Ikram, who has designs for his major jobs and his crafting/gathering classes, and rather than just shunt those designs into the gallery where they won't be seen, I thought it might be useful to create a layout that showcases the designs front and center!
    
    This was built using my Tabbed Profile code as a base, specifically building on the Design tab.  In addition to the main image and palette, I've also added individual turnaround images and made the detail images a little bigger.  As with the Tabbed Profile code, you can resize the different divs to suit your images.  Note that the images are specifically BACKGROUND IMAGES, not <img> tags!
    
    Have fun!
    
    == HOW DO I USE IT? ==
    Just edit each section as needed!  There are comments to clarify each part for you.
    
    == WHAT'S THE CATCH? ==
    Just keep my credit intact; that's all I ask.
    
    == COMMON EDITING TIPS ==
    1) You can change the particular Bootstrap colors by replacing the color classes (such as bg-dark).  If you would prefer to remove the Bootstrap colors and use your own colors, just remove the entire color class and, in the given "style" section, add "background:" followed by a color, either a hex color or rgb/rgba value.
    2) You can remove the capitalization of the titles by removing the "text-uppercase" class from a given section.
    3) You can use inline color styling by using <span></span> tags in tandem with either Bootstrap color classes or custom color styling.
	
-->
